news.title: Himachal Pradesh government proposes new township plan near Shimla
news.para: The estimated cost of the project, including land acquisition, is Rs 1,374 crore, town and country planning minister Rajesh Dharani stated in a written reply to Sudhir Sharma, the Congress MLA from Dharamshala.

news.title: Mumbai: Dharavi redevelopment project hits a roadblock over railway land rights
news.para: The Railway Land Development Authority (RLDA) that has signed a lease deed with the Dharavi Redevelopment Project/Slum Redevelopment Authority (DRP/SRA) has refused to allow the land to be sub-leased.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body races against time to collect Rs 700 crore property tax dues in 35 days
news.para: At a time when GHMC is reeling under financial crunch, the officials are under tremendous pressure to achieve the target set for property tax, which funds various development works.

news.title: Upto 100% hike in property rate proposed in Indore's 49 areas
news.para: The district evaluation committee led by collector Asheesh Singh saw senior district registrar Amresh Naydu proposing a rise in the present guideline of property rate to be implemented from April 1, 2024.

news.title: Complete projects on time or face penalties: Maharashtra CM
news.para: While congratulating the winners, Chief Minister Shinde expressed concerns over delays in housing projects and emphasized the need to fulfill the aspirations of applicants waiting for quality homes.

news.title: ED summons Hiranandani Group promoters in FEMA case on February 26
news.para: ​The Hiranandanis have been asked to depose at the central agency's office in Mumbai but they may choose to submit their primary responses through an authorised representative, they said.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance hopes to earn Rs 5,000 crore profit in FY24
news.para: ​The non-core business includes Loan Against Property (LAP) and affordable housing finance, LIC Housing Finance managing director and CEO Tribhuwan Adhikari told PTI in an interaction.

news.title: Haryana RERA warns Gurugram builders of penalty for delay in filing projects' QPR
news.para: Filing of quarterly progress reports (QPR) and annual audit reports (AARs) by real estate developers is a mandatory requirement under RERA Act 2016.

news.title: GST Council may soon clarify tax exemption to RERA
news.para: ​According to the official, RERA, which functions as a regulator as well as facilitator for the realty sector, is covered under Article 243G of the Constitution dealing with powers, authority and responsibilities of panchayats.

news.title: Noida authority's CEO appoints nodal officer for stuck housing projects
news.para: The move followed a visit by a delegation from the Confederation of Real Estate Developers Associations of India (Credai) to discuss problems the developers are facing.

news.title: Punjab chief town planner arrested for illegally passing housing projects
news.para: ​​The bureau arrested chief town planner (CTP) Pankaj Bawa after he along with Mohali-based Bajwa Developers Limited director J S Bajwa and revenue official Lekh Raj were booked.

news.title: EOW files case against Paramvir Developers for financial irregularities of Rs 78 crore
news.para: ​This will be the first time since its formation that the regulatory body registered a complaint with the EOW based on a forensic audit of the project. The EOW has estimated the fraud amount to be Rs 78 crore.

news.title: Delhi metro phase IV construction starts
news.para: These new trains are advanced vehicles, designed for a safe speed of 95 kmph and operational speed of 85 kmph with driverless features. Inspired by tricolours of the national flag, the door pillar for the saloon interior of the trains will sport a mix of saffron, white and green paint.

news.title: Ensure RERA norms are not flouted in deals: Orissa HC
news.para: The observation was made on Wednesday on a PIL seeking the court’s direction to the authorities for implementation of the Real Estate (Regulation & Development) Act, 2016 in respect of land deals under plotted schemes.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body seals five commercial properties in Burail
news.para: The sealing exercise was carried out after tax defaulters did not clear dues even after getting recovery notices and sealing notices.

news.title: Jaipur civic body attaches five properties over non-payment of UD tax
news.para: JMC-Heritage administration attached four properties in Hawa Mahal zone on Friday after the property owners did not respond to notices regarding timely payment of UD tax.

news.title: MNCs implement green building norms in New town and Sector V in Kolkata
news.para: According to the Indian Green Building Council (IGBC), meeting global green standards by reducing carbon footprint and using renewable energy has become mandatory for Indian MNCs to strike deals with their foreign counterparts.

news.title: RWAs of Secunderabad cantonment oppose new groundwater usage norms
news.para: “There is no provision in the draft to enable us to apply for a certificate of non-availability of adequate drinking water from SCB. This clause must be included in the draft,” a resident said.

news.title: Luxury & sustainable real estate takes center stage at The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2024
news.para: The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2024 held in Taj Santacruz, Mumbai on February 23, 2024 witnesses gathering of top real estate stakeholders sharing their views on some of the pertinent issues of the Indian real estate sector.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes eight illegal colonies on 12 acres
news.para: Four unauthorised colonies, carved out on permit line in the revenue estate of Bhondsi village — wherein 24 under-construction structures, 10 boundary walls, one aluminium gate factory and 600m of road network — were demolished.
